a143 9
situations (met any demons lately?).

\subsubsection{PB Fright Checks}

When encountering an entity whose PB is 5 or less, PC's should roll
against [Entity's PB] \x (PC's WP).  If they fail this roll they must
then roll on the Fright Table, with the most severe effect possible
panic.  The GM may choose to waive this check, eg. the party has met
this troll a dozen times already.
