Target flies into berserk rage. Immediately charges to attack the
object of his rage. If the source is not apparent will charge about
noisily looking for it. Add 10 to Strike Chance and subtract 10 from
Defense.
d22 10
a31 9
Target panics. Attempts to maximise their perceived safety in relation
io the source of few.  This usually involves fleeing as rapidly as
possible, but could include cowering at the centre of the party, jumping
into someone's arms or burying their head in the sand, etc.  While a
state of panic prevails, some sanity is present and the target would
not, for example, normally run off the edge of a cliff (although they
might be allowed to cast a flying spell to facilitate their escape -
at a suitable minus of coursee).  Add 5 to any subsequent rolls on the
fright table.
d34 3
a36 4
Target is frozen in fear.  May take no action until snapped out of it,
for example slapped on face, stabbed with a weapon, etc.  The target
can break out of it themselves by rolling less than or equal to
willpower. Target gets one roll per pulse after the first pulse.  Once
d38 1
