fright table rolls.
d41 4
a44 4
Target becomes hysterical. Stands and screams until snapped out of (as
for 77-90).  May take no other action.  On recovery, roll Dl00: 1--50
wary; 51--55 berserk; 56--100 panic. Add 10 to subsequent fright table
rolls.
d47 4
a50 4
Target becomes catatonic. Hair turns white, may take no
action. Recovery as for 77--90.  Upon recovery, roll D100: 1-26 wary;
27--31 berserk; 32--95 panic; 96--100 hysterical. Add 15 to subsequent
fright table rolls.
d53 2
a54 3
Target faints dead away (collapsing to the ground).  He remains
unconscious for [D + 6] minutes.  Add 15 to all subsequcni rolls on
the Fright Table this day.
d57 5
a61 5
Target suffers a heart attack. The result is the same as for 101--106
except that the target may not move about under his own power for the
remainder of the day and suffer a decrease of 2 in all characteristics
until he has spent one month resting in bed. Add 15 to all subsequent
rolls on the Fright Table this day.
d64 5
a68 4
Target suffers a heart attack and must have medical attention
(cardiovascular resuscitation) within one minute (12 pulses of combat)
or die. If he does survive, all subsequent rolls on the Fright Table
are increased by 20 this day.
